TabularLearner.feature_importance[source]

TabularLearner.feature_importance(x:TabularLearner, df=None, perm_func='base_error', metric='accuracy', bs=None, reverse=True, plot=True)

Calculate and plot the Feature Importance based on df

{% endraw %}

We can pass in sections of a DataFrame, but not a DataLoader. perm_func dictates how to calculate our importance, and reverse will determine how to sort the output

Example Usage

We'll run an example on the ADULT_SAMPLE dataset

{% raw %} 
from fastai2.tabular.all import *
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
path = untar_data(URLs.ADULT_SAMPLE)
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
df = pd.read_csv(path/'adult.csv')
splits = RandomSplitter()(range_of(df))
cat_names = ['workclass', 'education', 'marital-status', 'occupation', 'relationship', 'race']
cont_names = ['age', 'fnlwgt', 'education-num']
procs = [Categorify, FillMissing, Normalize]
y_names = 'salary'
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
to = TabularPandas(df, procs=procs, cat_names=cat_names, cont_names=cont_names,
                   y_names=y_names, splits=splits)
dls = to.dataloaders()
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
learn = tabular_learner(dls, layers=[200,100], metrics=accuracy)
learn.fit(1)
epoch train_loss valid_loss accuracy time
0 0.367516 0.363469 0.832002 00:03
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
imp = learn.feature_importance(df.iloc[:1000], bs=64, reverse=True, plot=True)
